      • runStarter

        public java.util.List<ActionType> runStarter(java.util.HashSet<ActionType> actionTypes,
                                             java.util.List<bwapi.Unit> units,
                                             int currentMinerals,
                                             int currentGas,
                                             bwapi.UnitType workerUnitType,
                                             int currentFrameTimeStamp)
        Function for starting a new simulation in the Simulator instance.
        Parameters:
        actionTypes - the ActionTypes that are going to be used in the simulation.
        units - the Units that are going to be used in the simulation.
        currentMinerals - the current gas count. Defines the basis for all gas dependent operations.
        currentGas - the current mineral count. Defines the basis for all mineral dependent operations.
        workerUnitType - the UnitType that defines the worker. Different for all Races.
        currentFrameTimeStamp - the current time stamp in frames.
        Returns:
        the List of ActionTypes that is the result of the Simulator simulation.

      • extractFreeAndWorkingTypeWrappers

        private static void extractFreeAndWorkingTypeWrappers(java.util.List<bwapi.Unit> units,
                                                      java.util.HashMap<TypeWrapper,java.lang.Integer> simulationTypesFree,
                                                      java.util.HashMap<TypeWrapper,java.util.List<bwapi.Pair<TypeWrapper,java.lang.Integer>>> simulationTypesWorking,
                                                      int currentFrameTimeStamp)
        Function for splitting a List of given Units in different categories (Free and working) as well as counting the specific types.
        Parameters:
        units - the Units that are going to be categorized.
        simulationTypesFree - the HashMap to which all free Units are going to be added to.
        simulationTypesWorking - the HashMap to which all working Units are going to be added to (As well as their result type and the time stamp).
        currentFrameTimeStamp - the current time stamp in frames.

      • addTypeWorking

        private static void addTypeWorking(java.util.HashMap<TypeWrapper,java.util.List<bwapi.Pair<TypeWrapper,java.lang.Integer>>> simulationUnitsWorking,
